# Patterns DVC must ignore. Learn more: https://dvc.org/doc/user-guide/dvcignore
#
# NOTE: the open-data CSVs are the project's deliverable and stay versioned in git
# (directly downloadable, no DVC/S3 needed). They are NOT pattern-ignored anymore —
# dvc.yaml declares them as `cache: false` pipeline outputs, which is the precise
# mechanism that keeps them DAG-tracked yet living in git (and a stray `dvc add` on a
# path already owned by a stage is rejected by DVC). A blanket data/**/*.csv ignore
# would instead make DVC refuse to track them as stage outputs at all.
